# Keep `docker build` reproducible: ignore anything that's produced locally or that
# would leak host-side state into the image. The Dockerfile's `COPY apps ./apps` and
# `COPY packages ./packages` rely on this to skip per-workspace node_modules, build
# outputs, and SQLite data.

# Dependency installs — re-installed inside the deps stage from the lockfile.
**/node_modules

# Build outputs — re-built inside the build stage.
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/dist
**/.tsbuildinfo

# Local runtime state — the container creates its own under the /app/data volume.
data
**/.pm2
**/*.log
**/logs

# Git / VCS — not needed at build time and bloats context.
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Local secrets — never bake into an image. `.env.example` IS shipped.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Editor / OS noise.
.DS_Store
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo

# Tests + coverage — not part of the runtime image.
**/coverage
**/__snapshots__
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.spec.tsx

# The marketing site (sentinello.org) — not part of the portal image. The Dockerfile builds only
# web + worker; keep homepage's source and screenshot assets out of the build context entirely.
apps/homepage

# Plans / scratch / docs that don't need to ship.
docs
docs/superpowers
.woc-ide
.llm
.cursor
.claude
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
demo-projects
README.md

# Docker meta — already on disk in the build context, no need to copy into image.
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.*.yml

# CI config — not used inside the image.
.github
